<center>''Level 322'' is the 323<sup>rd</sup> level of The Backrooms.</center>
<div style="background: rgba(25, 25, 25,0.5); color: #FFFFFF; border:3px solid; box-shadow: 7px 4px 0 #FFFFFF; padding:5px 10px; margin:1em; text-align:center;"><font size="6">Description</font></div>
{{Blurimage|file=Chamber322.jpg|caption=Chambers that leads to unknown.}}
''Level 322'' is a complex resembling old European dungeons, with surfaces appearing rusted and a highly variable layout that often leads to claustrophobic passages. The dungeons feature maze-like structures, with the overall interior design constructed from bricks made of rusted mineral stones. There are no lighting elements present, leaving the level in complete darkness. Additionally, the dungeons are multi-leveled and connected through irregularly designed stairways found in transitional areas. The dungeons can also open into small, empty rooms with no discernible design purpose.
{{Blurimage|file=Tunnel322.jpg|caption=Tunnels with stairs, rotten and forgotten.}}
The geometry of the level is unstable, much like [[Level 0]], and can completely disregard the rules of Euclidean geometry. This is demonstrated by the fact that entire sections of dungeons that have been traversed can suddenly be replaced with completely different sections of the level. It is believed to occur at speeds too fast to be perceived.
{{Blurimage|file=Void322.jpg|caption=The hole seemingly leads to what looks like [[The Void]], but is instead an exit.}}
Less frequently, the dungeons open into enclosed areas, frequently flanked by rows of parallel, closely set bars of metal. These areas are frequently found at the bottom of staircases or the junctions of corridors in dungeons, forming cul-de-sacs. Sometimes, these enclosed areas take the form of lines of prison-like rooms, joined side to side or opposite each other, to form corridors that resemble those of a prison. Inside, one can find stone furniture, fossilized human remains, and wooden crates. These crates occasionally contain wooden sticks and, less commonly, [[Object 44|Cashew Water]] bottles. Additionally, scratch marks and remnants of illegible inscriptions resembling Latin can be observed on the walls of these prison chambers.

''Level 322'' has high psychological impacts on wanderers due to an unknown cause. It is believed to be an effect of the environment at the level. Symptoms include whispers or incoherent voices heard from the darkness and dark human-like figures. These hallucinations may occur almost immediately after entering the level and tend to increase in intensity over time. Prolonged exposure to the level has been observed to severely impact mental health, with cases of gradual cognitive deterioration potentially leading to chronic schizophrenia. Many wanderers are thought to succumb to [[Phenomenon 35|Roth Syndrome]] as a result of these effects. The level also has a strong effect on mood, akin to those reported in [[Level 327]]. Prolonged exposure to the level tends to induce irrational aggression and euphoria, commonly associated with states of madness. Prolonged exposure can lead to motor reflex impairments and erratic abnormal behavior.

<div style="background: rgba(25, 25, 25,0.5); color: #FFFFFF; border:3px solid; box-shadow: 7px 4px 0 #FFFFFF; padding:5px 10px; margin:1em; text-align:center;"><font size="6">Environmental Hazards</font></div>

The atmosphere of ''Level 322'' is dense and foggy due to the high particle concentration in the air. It also contains a strong fetid odor, the source of which remains unknown. Reports indicate that as wanderers descend deeper into the level’s multi-leveled system, the air becomes increasingly heavy, and the atmospheric pressure rises. Moreover, the air in the level is sound-absorbing, thus average sound levels are extremely low. Echoes and the sounds of shifting stones are easily heard throughout the level, however.

Another notable environmental feature is the occasional collapses observed within the level. Although the stone bricks generally stick together tight, in time they shift and sometimes just vibrate in ways that make noises associated with their movement. Though this often stops of its own accord, there are times when brick walls give way and sometimes collapse, allowing parts of the dungeon to collapse, often leaving only empty space, sometimes like the caves of [[Level 8]], sometimes only a pile of rubble created by the fallen bricks.

Another threat is a reddish liquid that drips from the dungeon ceilings. The substance in question, which resembles both in appearance and composition [ DATA LOST ] and [[Object 12|Liquid Pain]], irritates and corrodes. Such liquids can either pool in little puddles throughout the level or land directly on wanderers with physical harm, and believed to contribute to the rusting pervading the level.

<div class="titleblock"><span class="titlebox">File - Note.pdf</span>
An accidental discovery in the level revealed that the minerals in the stones, along with high-electron metal particles, increase radiation and antimatter presence. Prolonged exposure to the level may lead to cancer, brain damage, and mental health issues. While this radiation could explain the mental health effects, the frequent sightings of anomalous entities suggest further investigation is needed.
<div align="right">''- September 6, 2013.''</div>
</div>

<div style="background: rgba(25, 25, 25,0.5); color: #FFFFFF; border:3px solid; box-shadow: 7px 4px 0 #FFFFFF; padding:5px 10px; margin:1em; text-align:center;"><font size="6">Discovery</font></div>

The first recorded discovery of the level is based on six pieces of paper found on a table in [[Level 323]] on April 24, 2012. These papers were written by an unknown wanderer whose current status remains uncertain. The discovery entries are presented below:
<div style="background-color:rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.5); margin:1em; padding:5px 10px; border:2px solid #FFFFFF; border-radius: 3px">
<div class="tabs vertical">
<ul class="tabs__caption">
<li class="active">Entry 1</li>
<li>Entry 2</li>
<li>Entry 3</li>
<li>Entry 4</li>
<li>Entry 5</li>
<li>Entry 6</li>
</ul>
<div class="tabs__content active"><center><big>-A New Level-</big></center>
I guess I got lucky and finally found a new level. To explain, while wandering around [[Level 321]], I found a chair partially embedded in the ground. When I interacted with it to investigate, I suddenly fell through the floor and ended up here. This place is incredibly dark and designed like a dungeon, with everything appearing rusty. Unfortunately, I don’t have a camera with me, but I’ll try to sketch the level’s appearance when I have the chance. My recommendation is to come here with some kind of flashlight. Anyway, I’ll explore the area and record any developments.

<div align="right">''- April 19, 2012.''</div></div>
<div class="tabs__content"><center><big>-Help-</big></center>
I’ve been here for a while and haven’t had the chance to write a new entry until now, but I’m writing as quickly as I can. This level is not safe! Its structure is highly unstable—just as erratic as those damn [[Level 0|yellow office walls]]. This cursed level made me lose my equipment bag. All I have left is a single bottle of [[Object 1|Almond Water]], one flashlight, and a matchbox, and I still have no idea how to escape. I also need to mention that this place is becoming extremely unsettling. I constantly feel like I’m being watched, and even worse, I keep hearing whispers nearby. I need help. I hope I can get out of here.

<div align="right">''- April 20, 2012.''</div></div>
<div class="tabs__content"><center><big>-Damn It!-</big></center>
I’m starting to think it was a mistake to come here. Last night, I was trying to rest in a corner of the dungeon when the whole place began shaking violently. At first, I thought it was an earthquake, but by the time I realized what was happening, it was too late. I barely managed to throw myself onto a staircase step, but the dungeon collapsed on itself. I was rationing my [[Object 1|Almond Water]] bottle, but unfortunately, it was crushed under the debris, and my spare batteries for the flashlight were lost as well. I don’t know what to do, but I think I need to move away from here since all that noise might attract something.

<div align="right">''- April 21, 2012.''</div></div>
<div class="tabs__content"><center><big>-Sleepless-</big></center>
I haven’t been able to get any sleep since the incident the other day. I feel extremely paranoid right now, and maybe it’s because of the lack of sleep, but I’ve started seeing black humanoid figures around me. However, one thing I’m certain of is that I’m not alone here. Every minute, I feel as if someone is right behind me. I’ve even heard footsteps nearby several times. On top of that, the air here is incredibly dense. It feels like I’m suffocating in humidity. My head is spinning, and I think I urgently need to find my lost supplies, or I won’t survive.

<div align="right">''- April 22, 2012.''</div></div>
<div class="tabs__content"><center><big>-Scared to Death-</big></center>
Now I know the source of those footsteps. I must have fainted from hours of sleeplessness, collapsing directly onto the ground. Fortunately, I woke up shortly after. When I checked my wristwatch, only a few minutes had passed. While trying to make sense of what had happened, I heard it—someone breathing right behind me. When I turned around, I saw a [[Phenomenon 35|Wretch]] staring directly at me. It tried to attack me, but I managed to fend it off by hitting it with my flashlight and escaping. I can still hear footsteps nearby, so I’ll stay hidden until it leaves.

<div align="right">''- April 23, 2012.''</div></div>
<div class="tabs__content"><center><big>-I Want to Leave-</big></center>
I can’t take it anymore. I’m exhausted, starving, and dehydrated. It’s relatively safe around me right now, but after hitting that creature with my flashlight, the flashlight stopped working properly. I think I damaged it, and now it doesn’t work at all. I’m using matches from my matchbox, but they burn out too quickly. A few hours ago, I found a bottle in a crate and, thinking it was [[Object 1|Almond Water]], I drank some of it, but it wasn’t. I don’t know what to do anymore. My muscles ache, and I don’t even have the mental strength to keep myself going. I feel like I’m slowly dying. I hope I can escape this place.

<div align="right">''- April 24, 2012.''</div></div>
</div>
</div>
<div style="background: rgba(25, 25, 25,0.5); color: #FFFFFF; border:3px solid; box-shadow: 7px 4px 0 #FFFFFF; padding:5px 10px; margin:1em; text-align:center;"><font size="6">Life Presence</font></div>

As the level is unstable, one can hardly find any alive beings. At times, certain wanderers can be found on the level, but they eventually become [[Phenomenon 35|Wretch]] due to [[Phenomenon 35|Roth Syndrome]]. Also there have been very few attempts at colonizing and building outposts, aside from the generally hazardous and unreliable state of the level, which likewise has forbidden extensive study of it by the [[M.E.G.]]. Because of this, teams will often quickly become disoriented, and objects placed within the level will vanish over a timeframe too long to measure; further study is urgently necessary.

<div style="background: rgba(25, 25, 25,0.5); color: #FFFFFF; border:3px solid; box-shadow: 7px 4px 0 #FFFFFF; padding:5px 10px; margin:1em; text-align:center;"><font size="6">Passageways</font></div>

To enter, No-clipping through the ground of an Empty Chamber at [[Level 828]] can lead one into this level. To exit, finding a hole and delving deeper into it will lead to [[Level 192]].
